.TH VITTEC 1 "May 2026" "vitte 0.1.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
vittec \- compatibility command for legacy Vitte workflows

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vittec
[\fIcommand\fR] [\fIoptions\fR] \fI<input>\fR

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vittec
is the compatibility frontend for the Vitte compiler toolchain.

It exists to preserve historical workflows, scripts, build systems,
continuous integration configurations, IDE integrations, shell aliases,
and automation originally written for older releases of the compiler.

Internally,
.B vittec
uses the same frontend, semantic analysis pipeline, type checker,
borrow checker, intermediate representations, runtime integration,
diagnostics engine, cache subsystem, and backend infrastructure as
.BR vitte (1).

No separate compiler implementation exists.

For all practical purposes:

.nf
vittec == vitte
.fi

except for command naming and compatibility behavior.

.SH COMPATIBILITY GUARANTEE

The Vitte project attempts to maintain long-term compatibility for
.B vittec
so that older projects continue to build without modification.

The compatibility layer covers:

.IP \(bu 2
historical command invocations

.IP \(bu 2
legacy automation scripts

.IP \(bu 2
older editor integrations

.IP \(bu 2
continuous integration systems

.IP \(bu 2
packaging environments

.IP \(bu 2
educational material

.IP \(bu 2
bootstrap compiler workflows

.SH ARCHITECTURE

The
.B vittec
command forwards execution to the modern compiler pipeline:

.nf
Source
  |
Lexer
  |
Parser
  |
AST
  |
Resolver
  |
Semantic Analysis
  |
Type Checker
  |
Borrow Checker
  |
HIR
  |
MIR
  |
IR
  |
Backend
  |
Linker
  |
Executable
.fi

All compiler passes are identical to those used by
.BR vitte (1).

